dy": "```\nIn [1]: from datalad.api import Dataset\nIn [2]: ds=Dataset('test').create()\n2016-10-20 10:36:45,655 [INFO   ] Creating a new annex repo at /tmp/test \nIn [3]: ds.repo.get_remotes()\nOut[3]: []\nIn [4]: ds.config.add('remote.whatever.something', 'ignore', where='local')\nIn [5]: ds.repo.get_remotes()\nOut[5]: [u'whatever']\n```\n\nIt seems that some uses of `get_remotes` assume that there would be at least a URL configured. Found one such case in #1018 \n\nMaybe we should consult other info too?\n\nI understand that there is `with_refs`, but there is a vacuum between \"I have a config variable\" and \"i have fetched stuff from a configured remote\".\n", "closed_by": {"login": "bpoldrack", "id": 10498301, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDk4MzAx", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10498301?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack", "html_url": "https://github.com/bpoldrack", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1036/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1036/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}